    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As a Washingtonian, I loved your story on feeling &#8220;so Seattle.&#8221; Your writing is simply amazing, Molly&#8230;engaging, clever, and sincere. I have sweet memories of crabbing a few times in my childhood with friends who had the equipment&#8230;racing around in a little speed boat on the choppy water to check the traps, simply watching my dad and his friend wear waders in Birch Bay as I floated along behind in a little dingy with my sister. And then the blessed times that friends would just show up at the door with extras from their catch. Now, in West Texas, I&#8217;m scared to touch seafood. I know it won&#8217;t taste the same and will only give me that same tight-chest feeling.</p>
    </div>

