    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The best crab I ever ate was hauled out of my dad&#8217;s crab pots on Coronet Bay off Whidbey Island in Washington.  We rushed the crabs back to my dad&#8217;s house and within an hour they were steaming in a propane-fired pot in his garage. I&#8217;ve eaten many crabs here in California, but none so sweet.</p>
    </div>

