    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I spent that same weekend enjoying crab myself &#8211; I went and hung out at my parents&#8217; house on Willapa Harbor on the coast of WA.  They&#8217;re out of town for a month, so their fridge was bare.  What could be an easier dinner than crab in the shell?   To me, crabs also relate to the holidays &#8211; there&#8217;s usually one around Christmas and I&#8217;ve started a tradition of crabs on New Year&#8217;s.  Probably one of things I&#8217;d miss the most if I ever left the NW.  Oh, that, and oysters, too &#8211; I brought a pint back with me to Portland to enjoy.</p>
    </div>

