    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;m sorry to comment randomly! I came here for asparagus ideas and found that you are an asparagus aficionadao. Much as I love asparagus <>au naturel<>, I was so taken by your asparagus &#8216;flan&#8217; (really more of a custard, to my way of thinking) that I had to try it. I don&#8217;t know whether I did it according to your standards but it certainly earned me some gracious comments!</p>
<p>However, what I really came here to say was that I have placed your RSS feed on my page next to FXCuisine &#8211; <a href="http://fxcuisine.com/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://fxcuisine.com/</a> &#8211; (which, if you haven&#8217;t already encountered, I really think you should!)</p>
<p>Here in the UK the best crab probably comes from Cromer, on the Eastern bulge, but I think it is basically the same as your Dungeness crab! It also goes remarkably well with asparagus.</p>
    </div>

